    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-05-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">857.014/28</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Norwegian Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bryn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note to Your Excellency’s
                    predecessor, dated April 21, 1922,<note n="8" xml:id="d531fn8">
                        <ref target="frus1923v02#pg_632">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 632</ref>.</note> I hereby have the
                    honor, acting under instructions from my Government, to inform the Government of
                    the United States of the fact that the Norwegian Meteorological Institute (<hi
                        rend="italic">Det Norske Meteorologiske Institut</hi>) has, with a view to
                    permanent occupation, extended its annexation on the Arctic island Jan Mayen,
                    mentioned in my above note, so that the annexation of the Institute is now
                    comprising the entire island of Jan Mayen.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Bryn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
